issue.title: [BUG] Function exports experiencing issues
issue.body:
I'm not sure what this issue is from, but an otherwise normal function export to JAX seems to give the following issue:
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/Users/mcranmer/venvs/main/lib/python3.8/site-packages/pysr/export_jax.py", line 67, in sympy2jaxtext
    _func = {**_jnp_func_lookup, **extra_jax_mappings}[expr.func]
KeyError: <class 'sympy.core.numbers.Half'>
```
Operators include "sqrt" and "square" - maybe from one of them? The other operators are unit-tested...
